# Development Guidelines

## Setup Requirements

1. Node.js environment
2. SQLite database
3. Local network access

## Code Style

- Use ES6+ features
- Follow camelCase naming convention
- Add JSDoc comments for functions
- Handle errors appropriately

## Testing

Before submitting changes:
1. Test device discovery
2. Verify file transfers work
3. Check database operations
4. Ensure cleanup works properly

## Security Considerations

1. Validate all file uploads
2. Sanitize device names
3. Clean up temporary files
4. Monitor WebSocket connections

## Performance

- Optimize large file transfers
- Clean up old database entries
- Monitor memory usage
- Handle concurrent connections efficiently

